"index_reference": "4428: corn",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A cereal crop cultivated for food use. An important agricultural crop in biblical times, it is mentioned frequently in Scripture.</p>\n<h2>The importance of corn</h2>\n<h3>It was a basic foodstuff</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:9\">PSA 65:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:42-2Kgs4:44\">2KI 4:42–4:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:24-Ezek36:31\">EZK 36:24–36:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:1-Matt12:8\">MAT 12:1–12:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:23-Mark2:28\">MRK 2:23–2:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:1-Luke6:5\">LUK 6:1–6:5</a></p>\n<h3>It was an important cereal crop</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:16\">PSA 72:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:1-Judg15:6\">JDG 15:1–15:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:11-Ps65:13\">PSA 65:11–65:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:16-Isa36:17\">ISA 36:16–36:17</a></p>\n<h2>Harvesting corn</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:26-Mark4:29\">MRK 4:26–4:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:9-Deut16:10\">DEU 16:9–16:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:22-Job24:24\">JOB 24:22–24:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:4-Isa17:6\">ISA 17:4–17:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:22\">JER 9:22</a></p>\n<h2>Legislation relating to corn</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:25\">DEU 23:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:6\">EXO 22:6</a></p>\n<h2>Corn featuring in dreams</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:5-Gen37:8\">GEN 37:5–37:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:5-Gen41:7\">GEN 41:5–41:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:22-Gen41:32\">GEN 41:22–41:32</a></p>\n<h2>The metaphorical use of corn</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos14:5-Hos14:7\">HOS 14:5–14:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:11-Jer50:13\">JER 50:11–50:13</a></p>",
